User: There is no function. I never set one up, unless it was through a cmd prompt with you recently. There is noting in Services or Jobs

Gemini: LET'S FOCUS ON DIAGNOSING WHY THE BUILD FAILED and why the function was not created.

PLEASE PERFORM THESE DIAGNOSTIC STEPS EXACTLY:

STEP 1: RE-EXAMINE TERMINAL OUTPUT of the LAST gcloud functions deploy COMMAND.

GO BACK to your TERMINAL WINDOW where you ran the gcloud functions deploy command.
SCROLL UP in the TERMINAL OUTPUT to the very beginning of the output from that last gcloud functions deploy command.
CAREFULLY READ through the ENTIRE TERMINAL OUTPUT from beginning to end.
LOOK for ANY LINES that contain the word "ERROR" (or "Error", or "error"). Copy all lines that look like error messages.
ALSO, look for any lines that contain the word "WARNING" (or "Warning", or "warning"). Copy any warning messages as well.
COPY and PASTE ALL ERROR AND WARNING MESSAGES from the TERMINAL OUTPUT here. Even if you think they are the same errors as before, please copy the full output again.
STEP 2: RE-RUN the gcloud functions deploy command.

In your TERMINAL, COPY and PASTE this exact command again (single line, no backslashes):

gcloud functions deploy ai-system-backend --runtime python310 --entry-point serve_health_check --trigger-http --allow-unauthenticated --region us-central1
PRESS ENTER to execute the command again.

OBSERVE the TERMINAL OUTPUT CAREFULLY as it runs.

ONCE IT FINISHES (whether it succeeds or fails), COPY the ENTIRE TERMINAL OUTPUT and PASTE it here. Please provide the complete output, from the start of the command to the end.

AFTER YOU COMPLETE STEP 1 and STEP 2, PLEASE PASTE THE TERMINAL OUTPUTS HERE.

WE NEED TO ANALYZE THE TERMINAL OUTPUTS CAREFULLY TO UNDERSTAND WHY THE DEPLOYMENT IS FAILING and WHY THE FUNCTION IS NOT BEING CREATED!

Let's get to the bottom of this! Go! Go! Go!
